{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/paper-review-swin-transformer","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"f9c79116-4bb0-5e6e-bc24-92f09770466a","html":"<p><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2103.14030\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Paper link</a></p>\n<p>Code available <a href=\"https://github.com/microsoft/Swin-Transformer\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">here</a> (no implementation at the moment of writing this review)</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/2a4bc/review_collage.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/8ac56/review_collage.webp 240w,\n/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/d3be9/review_collage.webp 480w,\n/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/e46b2/review_collage.webp 960w,\n/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/f992d/review_collage.webp 1440w,\n/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/882b9/review_collage.webp 1920w,\n/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/14846/review_collage.webp 3264w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/8ff5a/review_collage.png 240w,\n/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/e85cb/review_collage.png 480w,\n/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/d9199/review_collage.png 960w,\n/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/07a9c/review_collage.png 1440w,\n/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/29114/review_collage.png 1920w,\n/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/2a4bc/review_collage.png 3264w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/d9199/review_collage.png\"\n            alt=\"collage\"\n            title=\"collage\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>An amazing paper from Microsoft Research Asia presents a brand new vision Transformer called Swin Transformer that\ncan serve as a backbone just like usual CNNs in computer vision and Transformers in natural language processing (NLP).\n<br><br>\nThere are two main problems with the usage of Transformers for computer vision. Firstly, existing Transformer-based models have tokens of a fixed scale.\nHowever in contrast to the word tokens, visual elements can be different in scale.\nSecondly, computational complexity of self-attention is quadratic to image size, causing problems in vision tasks with dense\npredictions at the pixel level.\n<br><br>\nAuthors offer strategies to solve these challenges:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Hierarchical feature maps for convenient utilization of techniques like feature pyramid networks (FPN) or U-Net for dense predictions.</li>\n<li>Computing self-attention locally within non-overlapping windows with equal number of patches to achieve linear complexity.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 541px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ec9665d3f8311c899853d9b3528e0272/8af7b/fig_1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/ec9665d3f8311c899853d9b3528e0272/8ac56/fig_1.webp 240w,\n/static/ec9665d3f8311c899853d9b3528e0272/d3be9/fig_1.webp 480w,\n/static/ec9665d3f8311c899853d9b3528e0272/fd5d3/fig_1.webp 541w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 541px) 100vw, 541px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/ec9665d3f8311c899853d9b3528e0272/09b79/fig_1.jpg 240w,\n/static/ec9665d3f8311c899853d9b3528e0272/7cc5e/fig_1.jpg 480w,\n/static/ec9665d3f8311c899853d9b3528e0272/8af7b/fig_1.jpg 541w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 541px) 100vw, 541px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/ec9665d3f8311c899853d9b3528e0272/8af7b/fig_1.jpg\"\n            alt=\"fig 1\"\n            title=\"fig 1\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Swin Transformer outperformes current state-of-the-art approaches on both COCO object detection and ADE20K semantic segmentation\nwhile achieving the best speed-accuracy trade-off on image classification.</p>\n<h2 id=\"methods\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#methods\" aria-label=\"methods permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Methods</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d072d7db7677f8514689c71645354712/70a80/fig_3.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 33.33333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/d072d7db7677f8514689c71645354712/8ac56/fig_3.webp 240w,\n/static/d072d7db7677f8514689c71645354712/d3be9/fig_3.webp 480w,\n/static/d072d7db7677f8514689c71645354712/e46b2/fig_3.webp 960w,\n/static/d072d7db7677f8514689c71645354712/4a689/fig_3.webp 1133w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/d072d7db7677f8514689c71645354712/09b79/fig_3.jpg 240w,\n/static/d072d7db7677f8514689c71645354712/7cc5e/fig_3.jpg 480w,\n/static/d072d7db7677f8514689c71645354712/6a068/fig_3.jpg 960w,\n/static/d072d7db7677f8514689c71645354712/70a80/fig_3.jpg 1133w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/d072d7db7677f8514689c71645354712/6a068/fig_3.jpg\"\n            alt=\"fig 3\"\n            title=\"fig 3\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"overall-architecture\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#overall-architecture\" aria-label=\"overall architecture permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Overall Architecture</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>Splitting RGB image into non-overlapping patches (tokens).</li>\n<li>Applying linear embedding layer to translate raw feature into an arbitrary dimension.</li>\n<li>Applying several Swin Transformer blocks with modified self-attention computation and maintaining the number of tokens.</li>\n<li>Reducing number of tokens by patch merging layers creating the same feature map resolutions like those in common CNNs.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4 id=\"shifted-window-based-self-attention\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#shifted-window-based-self-attention\" aria-label=\"shifted window based self attention permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Shifted Window based Self-Attention</h4>\n<p>Standard global self-attention is not quite suitable for representations of high-resolution images because of quadratic complexity.\nAuthors propose to compute self-attention within local windows.<br>\nHere is the comparison of computational complexities of a global MSE module and a new window-based one</p>\n<ol>\n<li>M is the size of <em>M x M</em> patch</li>\n<li>Images consists of <em>h x w</em> patches</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 532px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b196ce2767ca3f962e42fa7c4c91df6b/89a37/complexities.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 14.583333333333334%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/b196ce2767ca3f962e42fa7c4c91df6b/8ac56/complexities.webp 240w,\n/static/b196ce2767ca3f962e42fa7c4c91df6b/d3be9/complexities.webp 480w,\n/static/b196ce2767ca3f962e42fa7c4c91df6b/b5f85/complexities.webp 532w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 532px) 100vw, 532px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/b196ce2767ca3f962e42fa7c4c91df6b/8ff5a/complexities.png 240w,\n/static/b196ce2767ca3f962e42fa7c4c91df6b/e85cb/complexities.png 480w,\n/static/b196ce2767ca3f962e42fa7c4c91df6b/89a37/complexities.png 532w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 532px) 100vw, 532px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/b196ce2767ca3f962e42fa7c4c91df6b/89a37/complexities.png\"\n            alt=\"complexities\"\n            title=\"complexities\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Moreover, there is an idea about transferring shifted window partitioning strategy to the next MSA block to create\nadditional connections across windows.<br>\nComputation of Swin Transformer blocks:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 429px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/17240c57f8a0c21bf555d1d03aee7aa5/3d026/swin_blocks.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 38.33333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/17240c57f8a0c21bf555d1d03aee7aa5/8ac56/swin_blocks.webp 240w,\n/static/17240c57f8a0c21bf555d1d03aee7aa5/649fd/swin_blocks.webp 429w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 429px) 100vw, 429px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/17240c57f8a0c21bf555d1d03aee7aa5/8ff5a/swin_blocks.png 240w,\n/static/17240c57f8a0c21bf555d1d03aee7aa5/3d026/swin_blocks.png 429w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 429px) 100vw, 429px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/17240c57f8a0c21bf555d1d03aee7aa5/3d026/swin_blocks.png\"\n            alt=\"swin_blocks\"\n            title=\"swin_blocks\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Shifted window partitioning will result in more windows and some of these windows will be smaller than <em>M x M</em>.\nSo, authors propose efficient batch computation approach with cyclic shifting toward the top-left direction.\nSince batched window might be created of sub-windows which are not adjacent in the feature map, mask is applied.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 563px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/af1e9e9f2bca03960efe1f67999126d9/7cb89/batched.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 38.75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/af1e9e9f2bca03960efe1f67999126d9/8ac56/batched.webp 240w,\n/static/af1e9e9f2bca03960efe1f67999126d9/d3be9/batched.webp 480w,\n/static/af1e9e9f2bca03960efe1f67999126d9/a1a69/batched.webp 563w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 563px) 100vw, 563px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/af1e9e9f2bca03960efe1f67999126d9/8ff5a/batched.png 240w,\n/static/af1e9e9f2bca03960efe1f67999126d9/e85cb/batched.png 480w,\n/static/af1e9e9f2bca03960efe1f67999126d9/7cb89/batched.png 563w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 563px) 100vw, 563px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/af1e9e9f2bca03960efe1f67999126d9/7cb89/batched.png\"\n            alt=\"batched\"\n            title=\"batched\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Also, relative position bias is used</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 513px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9ab84df6880e41f1e08597efefacf130/267f6/bias.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.583333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/9ab84df6880e41f1e08597efefacf130/8ac56/bias.webp 240w,\n/static/9ab84df6880e41f1e08597efefacf130/d3be9/bias.webp 480w,\n/static/9ab84df6880e41f1e08597efefacf130/3be34/bias.webp 513w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 513px) 100vw, 513px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/9ab84df6880e41f1e08597efefacf130/8ff5a/bias.png 240w,\n/static/9ab84df6880e41f1e08597efefacf130/e85cb/bias.png 480w,\n/static/9ab84df6880e41f1e08597efefacf130/267f6/bias.png 513w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 513px) 100vw, 513px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/9ab84df6880e41f1e08597efefacf130/267f6/bias.png\"\n            alt=\"bias\"\n            title=\"bias\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"experiments\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#experiments\" aria-label=\"experiments permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Experiments</h2>\n<p>Experiments were made on ImageNet-1K image classification, COCO object detection and ADE20K semantic segmentation.\nImageNet-22K was used for pre-training and ImageNet-1K for fine-tuning.\n<br><br>\nHere we can see that Swin Transformers achieve great speed-accuracy trade-off compared with the state-of-the-art CNNs.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 568px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a43f66f08da6e30c44de8a38ee588190/10e91/exp1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 142.91666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/a43f66f08da6e30c44de8a38ee588190/8ac56/exp1.webp 240w,\n/static/a43f66f08da6e30c44de8a38ee588190/d3be9/exp1.webp 480w,\n/static/a43f66f08da6e30c44de8a38ee588190/bebff/exp1.webp 568w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 568px) 100vw, 568px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/a43f66f08da6e30c44de8a38ee588190/8ff5a/exp1.png 240w,\n/static/a43f66f08da6e30c44de8a38ee588190/e85cb/exp1.png 480w,\n/static/a43f66f08da6e30c44de8a38ee588190/10e91/exp1.png 568w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 568px) 100vw, 568px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/a43f66f08da6e30c44de8a38ee588190/10e91/exp1.png\"\n            alt=\"exp 1\"\n            title=\"exp 1\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Swin Transformers scores better compared with ResNet-50, ResNeXt and DeiT as a backbone for Cascade Mask R-CNN and other detection models.\nAlso the inference speed is much higher than DeiT’s because of linear complexity to input image size.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 536px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/54029cdd57a847ebe826e3fe42e255a7/2d920/exp2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 170.83333333333334%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/54029cdd57a847ebe826e3fe42e255a7/8ac56/exp2.webp 240w,\n/static/54029cdd57a847ebe826e3fe42e255a7/d3be9/exp2.webp 480w,\n/static/54029cdd57a847ebe826e3fe42e255a7/c5a1c/exp2.webp 536w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 536px) 100vw, 536px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/54029cdd57a847ebe826e3fe42e255a7/8ff5a/exp2.png 240w,\n/static/54029cdd57a847ebe826e3fe42e255a7/e85cb/exp2.png 480w,\n/static/54029cdd57a847ebe826e3fe42e255a7/2d920/exp2.png 536w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 536px) 100vw, 536px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/54029cdd57a847ebe826e3fe42e255a7/2d920/exp2.png\"\n            alt=\"exp 2\"\n            title=\"exp 2\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Proposed model surpasses other backbones in ADE20K too. </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 542px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a97e43efbc9c099f6096387d31f68350/c0388/exp3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 95.83333333333334%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/a97e43efbc9c099f6096387d31f68350/8ac56/exp3.webp 240w,\n/static/a97e43efbc9c099f6096387d31f68350/d3be9/exp3.webp 480w,\n/static/a97e43efbc9c099f6096387d31f68350/3f954/exp3.webp 542w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 542px) 100vw, 542px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/a97e43efbc9c099f6096387d31f68350/8ff5a/exp3.png 240w,\n/static/a97e43efbc9c099f6096387d31f68350/e85cb/exp3.png 480w,\n/static/a97e43efbc9c099f6096387d31f68350/c0388/exp3.png 542w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 542px) 100vw, 542px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/a97e43efbc9c099f6096387d31f68350/c0388/exp3.png\"\n            alt=\"exp 3\"\n            title=\"exp 3\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Finally, there is an interesting ablation study that shows us that shifted window approach outperforms single window\npartitioning with relatively small latency overhead.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 516px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c3f4a4bf5e822957deea2784efffbcf8/75dcb/exp4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 77.91666666666667%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/c3f4a4bf5e822957deea2784efffbcf8/8ac56/exp4.webp 240w,\n/static/c3f4a4bf5e822957deea2784efffbcf8/d3be9/exp4.webp 480w,\n/static/c3f4a4bf5e822957deea2784efffbcf8/5f588/exp4.webp 516w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 516px) 100vw, 516px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/c3f4a4bf5e822957deea2784efffbcf8/8ff5a/exp4.png 240w,\n/static/c3f4a4bf5e822957deea2784efffbcf8/e85cb/exp4.png 480w,\n/static/c3f4a4bf5e822957deea2784efffbcf8/75dcb/exp4.png 516w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 516px) 100vw, 516px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/c3f4a4bf5e822957deea2784efffbcf8/75dcb/exp4.png\"\n            alt=\"exp 4\"\n            title=\"exp 4\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 519px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/afe8fc9d316f2914f9625bc007354246/b23ad/exp5.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 88.33333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/afe8fc9d316f2914f9625bc007354246/8ac56/exp5.webp 240w,\n/static/afe8fc9d316f2914f9625bc007354246/d3be9/exp5.webp 480w,\n/static/afe8fc9d316f2914f9625bc007354246/ad2dd/exp5.webp 519w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 519px) 100vw, 519px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/afe8fc9d316f2914f9625bc007354246/8ff5a/exp5.png 240w,\n/static/afe8fc9d316f2914f9625bc007354246/e85cb/exp5.png 480w,\n/static/afe8fc9d316f2914f9625bc007354246/b23ad/exp5.png 519w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 519px) 100vw, 519px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/afe8fc9d316f2914f9625bc007354246/b23ad/exp5.png\"\n            alt=\"exp 5\"\n            title=\"exp 5\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"conclusion\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-label=\"conclusion permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>I find this paper captivating and useful since it opens new possibilities of developing a unified architecture for\ncomputer vision and natural language processing tasks, which can benefit both fields and accelerate shared research.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/paper-review-swin-transformer","tagSlugs":["/tag/computer-vision/","/tag/image-classification/","/tag/instance-segmentation/","/tag/object-detection/","/tag/semantic-segmentation/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-03-27T23:46:37.121Z","description":"My review of the paper Swin Transformer: Hierarchical Vision Transformer using Shifted Windows","tags":["Computer Vision","Image Classification","Instance Segmentation","Object Detection","Semantic Segmentation"],"title":"Paper Review: Swin Transformer: Hierarchical Vision Transformer using Shifted Windows","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/4af7e5250004a1eec5e494d4e3f363f1/review_collage.png"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/paper-review-swin-transformer"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","401334301","825871152"]}